, recent studies have shown how completely interconnected Anglo-Latin and Old English literary traditions are.Old English Literature and the Old Testament considers the importance of the Old Testament from a variety of disciplinary perspectives, from comparative to intertextual and historical. Though the essays focus on individual works, authors, or trends, including the Interrogationes Sigewulfi, Genesis A, and Daniel, each ultimately speaks to the vernacular corpus as a whole, suggesting approaches and methodologies for further study.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh1 aElliot, Michael D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFleming, Damian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFox, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFox, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHarris, Stephen J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoole, Russell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPortnoy, Phyllis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharma, Manish, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharma, Manish, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSzarmach, Paul E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aToswell, M. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWaugh, Robin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWright, Charles D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZacher, Samantha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781442664296